    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The homeopathic remedy consisting of Arnica and Bellis perennis have been shown in a previous
      pilot study (n=33) to reduce blood loss during the third stage of delivery, when compared
      with placebo treatment. The purpose of this study is to repeat the previous methodology, this
      time on a larger population.

      210 parturients will be randomized to one of three groups: Arnica montana C6 and Bellis
      perennis C6 (n=70), Arnica montana C30 and Bellis perennis C30 (n=70), or double placebo
      (n=70).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
